  "text": "Mirage BRMS is made of PDLLA of which d (dextro-rotary)-isomer constitutes <5% of the total polylactic acid (PLA), coated with a biodegradable PLA delivering sirolimus. In the manufacturing process of Mirage scaffold, the polylactide monofilaments are winded and the helix-coiled structures are attached by longitudinal spine microfibers (Fig. 1) . The struts of Mirage have circular shape with thickness of 125 µm in scaffolds with diameter ≤3 mm (Mirage-125), and 150 µm in scaffolds with diameter ≥3.5 mm (Mirage-150). The helicoidal design is tightened by longitudinal spine microfibers providing radial strength for the Mirage (148.54 kPa) comparable to the Absorb (148.00 kPa) [CITATION_1] . ",
